This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with authorship attribution and verification using language models. It could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves machine learning techniques for detecting sockpuppets. The paper also deals with cybersecurity and deception, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper deals with retrieving hidden samples in the unlabeled test set. Finally, the paper could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it deals with detecting deceptive opinion spam, which is a prevalent problem in social media.
